cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CR 

This paper discusses the issues related to computer vision technology and the datasets used for its development. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the need for fairer datasets, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of ontology and vocabulary, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the issue of misbehavior of computer vision models, which can be related to the sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
